There is created the Tobacco Master Settlement Agreement Compliance Advisory Board in the Department of Law. The board shall be composed of six (6) members as follows:
The Attorney General, or the Attorney General's designee;
The secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services, or the secretary's designee;
The Commissioner of Agriculture, or the Commissioner's designee;
The secretary of the Public Protection Cabinet, or the secretary's designee; and
Two (2) citizens at large appointed by the Attorney General.
